<span id="freeTextContainer8566951599065956156">I think your review from an objective standpoint doesn’t warrant a one star review, as others have pointed out, you seem to have a major issue with th</span>
  <span id="freeText8566951599065956156" style="display:none">I think your review from an objective standpoint doesn’t warrant a one star review, as others have pointed out, you seem to have a major issue with the author rather than the work. Just judging by your first two paragraphs in the review. <br /><br />For whatever reason you had an incredibly fixated attitude on Kvothe describing his mom as beautiful and his student Bast being described the same way. How does it bear on the books work? You said yourself there’s nothing wrong with it but insist on writing an entire paragraph chewing it up. <br /><br />Next, I’ll concede that the third person narration gets slightly doozy at the beginning, but since the majority of the story is in first person it isn’t an issue throughout the majority of the story (you said yourself the meat is pretty good)<br /><br />Lastly, you said that since Kvothe is by his nature a Deus Ex Machina. An unfair assumption considering you barely made it through a fourth of the novel. He is described as such, but as he delves into his story to reveal the man behind this “legendary/mythical” character. In itself I find it extremely interesting and original, a lot of our folklore and legends have this larger than life characters (think Gilgamesh) that probably accomplished something interesting, but their stories got hyperbolic as time went on. <br /><br />I don’t really mind at the end of the day you’re entitled to your review, but when the majority of your post is based on perceived homoeroticism and Oedipus Complex and judging the story and character development solely based on 1/4th of the novel I can’t take it seriously. The narration style critique is valid, and some points here and there are kind of annoying (sometimes Kvothe will say he can’t recall certain parts of a story, but will recall the most mundane conversations and events perfectly…. This is probably my biggest gripe)<br /><br />1/5 review.</span>
