<div id="review_1367004050" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1367004050" />
    <a title="Charlotte" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11475773-charlotte"><img alt="Charlotte" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1613443590p2/11475773.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1367004050?book_show_action=true">Aug 18, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Charlotte" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Charlotte" href="/user/show/11475773-charlotte">Charlotte</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11475773-charlotte?shelf=proof-that-im-not-misandrist">proof-that-im-not-misandrist</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11475773-charlotte?shelf=epic-fantasy">epic-fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1367004050" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4836197937734512865">Exclusive footage of me thinking one negative review of this book will have any impact when it sits at 4.5 stars with over half a million reviews:<br/> <img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1573625190ra/28442483.gif' width='300' height='300' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/> <br/><br/>So, this book. Here&apos;s my take: Dickens orphan becomes Harry Potter except the magic system is ripped off from Le Guin&apos;s Earthsea, also the Dickens orphan is a raging Gary Stu and a deeply unlikable, conceited little fuckhead. &quot;Oh but Charlotte, that&apos;s the POINT so therefore it&apos;s actually good!!!!&quot; you insist. Well, first of all, hearing good sir Patr</span>
  <span id="freeText4836197937734512865" style="display:none">Exclusive footage of me thinking one negative review of this book will have any impact when it sits at 4.5 stars with over half a million reviews:<br> <img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1573625190ra/28442483.gif" width="300" height="300" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br>So, this book. Here's my take: Dickens orphan becomes Harry Potter except the magic system is ripped off from Le Guin's Earthsea, also the Dickens orphan is a raging Gary Stu and a deeply unlikable, conceited little fuckhead. "Oh but Charlotte, that's the POINT so therefore it's actually good!!!!" you insist. Well, first of all, hearing good sir Patrick Rothfuss bloviate on and on about any given subject on the Internet makes the supposition that Kvothe is a dick on purpose a DEEPLY suspect one in my eyes. Second of all, that still doesn't fucking make it enjoyable to read about a little shithead for hundreds of pages!!!!!<br><br>I'd also point out that all of the female characters exist to orbit around the Dickens orphan, serve the plot in no meaningful way and flirt with Dickens orphan constantly except for the one who's a little child. I'm pretty sure I eventually just started dissociating every time my fucking nemesis Denna walzted into the story again to slow its progress to a complete halt for another 20 pages or so. But I really shouldn't complain, because the gender/sex shit in the second book? Oh, god. Where to even begin? (Don't worry, I've dedicated <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1367003870" rel="nofollow noopener">another</a>, even lengthier rant, to that book's faults!)<br><br>The world-building? Paltry, and the only interesting bits get glossed over so that we can keep worshiping Kvothe for hundreds of pages. The rest of the cast? ALSO just exist to glorify Kvothe or prove how horrible they are because they don't glorify him. The prose? Okay, this might be a hot take, but I'm not exactly freaking out about it. You can write with the prettiest language in the world (which this is not, by the way) and if you don't have anything compelling to say I'm still gonna call you out on your shit. <br><br>I'm now going to recommend books that do all the stuff that The Name of the Wind is celebrated for, but BETTER. AND THEY'RE ALL WRITTEN BY WOMEN!!!!<br>For beautiful fantasy prose: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12814333.A_Stranger_in_Olondria" title="A Stranger in Olondria by Sofia Samatar" rel="nofollow noopener">A Stranger in Olondria</a> by Sofia Samatar, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/202769.In_the_Night_Garden__The_Orphan_s_Tales___1_" title="In the Night Garden (The Orphan's Tales, #1) by Catherynne M. Valente" rel="nofollow noopener">In the Night Garden</a> by Catherynne Valente, and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/81069.The_Forgotten_Beasts_of_Eld" title="The Forgotten Beasts of Eld by Patricia A. McKillip" rel="nofollow noopener">The Forgotten Beasts of Eld</a> by Patricia McKillip.<br>For the same framing device of a jaded, broken man looking back upon his adventures and telling his tale: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/77197.Assassin_s_Apprentice__Farseer_Trilogy___1_" title="Assassin's Apprentice (Farseer Trilogy, #1) by Robin Hobb" rel="nofollow noopener">Assassin's Apprentice</a> and the ensuing Fitz books by Robin Hobb.<br>For the cool naming magic system: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13642.A_Wizard_of_Earthsea__Earthsea_Cycle__1_" title="A Wizard of Earthsea (Earthsea Cycle #1) by Ursula K. Le Guin" rel="nofollow noopener">A Wizard of Earthsea</a> and the other Earthsea books by Ursula Le Guin.<br>For boarding school drama and adventures: <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/222837.Inda__Inda___1_" title="Inda (Inda, #1) by Sherwood Smith" rel="nofollow noopener">Inda</a> by Sherwood Smith. <br>Also I read this entire book and its sequel aloud to my awful high school boyfriend because I was an IDIOT in high school. Fuck you, Zac, and fuck this book!!!!!!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="4836197937734512865" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


